&nbsp;
LOI – Pending/Open Cases
&nbsp;
Previously Reported Issues :
******************************
1. Delay/Inconsistency in Order Import (Date Filter Issue)
  When filtering orders for a specific date, not all orders placed on that date are displayed in the app. Some missing orders only appear when the date range is adjusted with +/- 1 day. (i.e; filtering from the previous day to the next day).  2. Fulfilled Orders Showing Under "Not to Ship"
  Orders that have already been fulfilled are appearing in the Not to Ship section or their status is being changed to Not to Ship.  3. Duplicate Packages / Labels Created
  Duplicate packages and shipping labels are being generated for certain orders.  4. Archived &amp; Voided Orders Being Imported
  Orders with: Order Status = Archived &amp; Payment Status = Voided, should ideally not be imported into the app. However, these orders are currently being imported and remain in the Processing status.  5. Fulfillment Failed with "Order is already fulfilled" error but the order was never Fulfilled.
  Order: #45296293 A shipping label was created and a fulfillment attempt was made on June 10. The fulfillment failed with the error: "Order is already fulfilled." However, after reviewing the Shopify order timeline, the order was never fulfilled—neither manually nor by our app.  Impact: The merchant had to refund the customer because the order was never fulfilled in Shopify, even though the product had already been shipped, resulting in financial loss.
&nbsp;
6. Label Created Orders Updated as Cancelled in the app.
  Our app is currently updating the status of "Label Created" orders to Cancelled whenever the corresponding order is cancelled in Shopify, even though a shipping label has already been created. This is incorrect.

Expected behavior:
Once a shipping label has been created, the app should not update the order status to Cancelled, even if the corresponding Shopify order is later cancelled. The order should retain its post-label status (for example, Label Created).  7. Shipping Zone (Postcode-Based) Using Billing Address Instead of Shipping Address
  Order: #45307249  Issue: Amazon Shipping was not assigned even though the shipping postcode matches the configured shipping zone.
  Shipping Postcode: 452005  Billing Postcode: 411015  The shipping zone is configured for 452005, so Amazon Shipping should have been assigned.
From our observation, it appears that the app is validating the Billing Address postcode instead of the Shipping Address postcode while matching shipping zones.
&nbsp;
&nbsp;
New requests/issues :
******************************
&nbsp;
8. Duplicate Label Generation Across Multiple Carriers
  Order #45306773, both Delhivery and Xpressbees labels were generated at the same time for this order. Customer mentioned that they have not made any changes from their end, please check why 2 labels with 2 different carriers were created for this order.  &nbsp;
9. Labels Created for Cancelled orders
  The following 9 orders were cancelled on July 4th in Shopify but the customer was able to create the labels for these orders this morning. There could be more but we found these 9 as of now.
&nbsp;#45310766, #45310758, #45310752, #45310653, #45310641, #45310610, #45310577, #45310566, #45310558  &nbsp;
10. Order Report for last 6 months - including the "Package Weight" column for all the orders.
&nbsp;
11. &nbsp;Order #45290681 is missing in the Order Report.
&nbsp;
12. &nbsp;Issue with Fulfillments : Multiple fulfillment-related inconsistencies are being observed.
&nbsp;Case 1. Fulfilled Orders Showing as "Fulfillment Failed"
  Some orders that have already been fulfilled are appearing under Fulfillment Failed without any valid reason or clear explanation. Ex: order #45308148.  Case 2. &nbsp;Excessive Number of Fulfillment Failures
  We are seeing 2635 orders in "Fulfillment Failed" view for the last 1 month from June 6 to July 6 in the app. Please check, those many failures are alarming and don't seem accurate.
Ex: 45308148 is fulfilled by the app and is in Fulfilled status in Shopify but why is it in Fulfillment Failed status in the app and why does Fulfillment summary say "Order is already Fulfilled"?  Case 3. &nbsp;Incorrect Fulfillment Status &amp; incorrect Failure error messages
  Currently, orders where fulfillment has failed are also updated as Fulfilled in the app, ideally the status for such orders must be Fulfillment Failed. This is making it impossible for the Fulfillment team to identify these Fulfillment failed orders to take the necessary actions from their end.   The app displays a generic error "Order is already fulfilled" for multiple fulfillment failures, even when the actual reason is different.  For example, if a Shopify order is cancelled after a shipping label has been created, the fulfillment fails because the order was cancelled, not because it was already fulfilled. The failure summary should reflect the actual reason to help merchants troubleshoot the issue accurately.   &nbsp;
